  "markdown": "[home](https://www.bluequbit.io/) / [BLOG](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog) / BlueQubit\u2019s Algorithm Chosen by DARPA\nOur Quantum Advantage challenge with $20,000 BTC award is live.\n[More Details \u2192](https://app.bluequbit.io/hackathons/GFgHTGbTylwmMsCp)\n[![Logo Deqart](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/63a042ea84d8d44f97a1cc3e_Group%2097846.svg)](https://www.bluequbit.io/)\n[Home](https://www.bluequbit.io/)[Hackathons](https://www.bluequbit.io/quantum-advantage-challenge)[Pricing](https://www.bluequbit.io/pricing)[Platform](https://www.bluequbit.io/platform)[Blog](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog)[Research](https://www.bluequbit.io/research)[Contact Us](https://www.bluequbit.io/contact-us)[Platform Access](https://app.bluequbit.io/)\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/639adfd6b9bb747186953ef8_Icons.svg)![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/63e8e60dbe8e5c311ed976e2_icon_Close.svg)\n# BlueQubit\u2019s Algorithm Chosen by DARPA\nDecember 7, 2023\n\u2022\n5 min\nread\n[![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63d774102fb109fd799a5006/68daeb8dc77de81407588994_hayk_blog_img.png) Hayk Tepanyan Co-founder & CTO ](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog-author/hayk-tepanyan)\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63d774102fb109fd799a5006/6571e5a0ffe68d89cc8c783c_Press-Release-Bluequbit-Darpa.jpg)\n[BlueQubit Inc](https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bluequbit.io%2F&esheet=53650435&newsitemid=20231022224311&lan=en-US&anchor=BlueQubit+Inc&index=1&md5=6dadecde440cffa628ea36ff2d5eb620)., a technology company building [cloud-based quantum computing software](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog/quantum-computing-software-platforms), is proud to announce its selection for the prestigious Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA) project under the Imagining Practical Applications for a Quantum Tomorrow (IMPAQT) program. This recognition emphasizes the company\u2019s unwavering commitment to revolutionizing the quantum computing landscape, with a focus on development of quantum AI/ML algorithms for Noisy Intermediate-Scale Quantum (NISQ) devices.\nExperience quantum computing firsthand\n[Try the App](https://app.bluequbit.io/?utm_source=blog&utm_medium=cta&utm_campaign=mini-banner&utm_content=top-cta)\nDARPA has identified BlueQubit's objective of addressing challenges faced by classical computers. _\"As technology continues to progress, we've identified areas where classical methods fall short, particularly in Gibbs sampling, that are pivotal in numerous scientific, commercial, and defense applications.\"_**- Hrant Gharibyan, CEO at BlueQubit Inc.**\nA notable challenge has been in areas like cybersecurity in defense and training of large AI models. With the advent of quantum hardware boasting more than 100 qubits and 10,000 two-qubit gates, new horizons of solutions are emerging.\n_\"We're venturing into uncharted territories, focusing on hybrid computing environments. Quantum/classical hybrid algorithms, like QAOA, are the game-changers we're betting on.\"_**- Hayk Tepanyan, CTO at BlueQubit Inc**. These algorithms are designed to maximize the potential of full NISQ devices and find solutions without necessitating fault-tolerant quantum computers.\nParticularly noteworthy is BlueQubit's collaboration with the renowned quantum hardware company, QuEra. Their shared expertise on neutral-atom quantum computers \u2013 known for their scalability and improved gate fidelity \u2013 is central to the project.\n_\"We're on the cusp of a quantum leap in computing, and the DARPA IMPAQT award is a testament to the potential our team brings,\"_ **- Hrant Gharibyan.** BlueQubit, with its collaborative network of esteemed researchers from leading US institutions and tech maestros in high-performance computing, is poised to overcome classical limitations and march toward quantum advantage with innovation in hybrid quantum/classical computing approach.\nBlueQubit Inc. extends its gratitude to DARPA for this opportunity and remains steadfast in its mission: pushing the boundaries of quantum computing and setting new industry standards.\nAbout BlueQubit:\n[BlueQubit](https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bluequbit.io%2F&esheet=53650435&newsitemid=20231022224311&lan=en-US&anchor=BlueQubit&index=2&md5=4d1debb64337c8b618a5e4e131eddfe5) is a technology start-up based in California that builds a [quantum software platform](https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&url=https%3A%2F%2Fapp.bluequbit.io%2F&esheet=53650435&newsitemid=20231022224311&lan=en-US&anchor=quantum+software+platform&index=3&md5=74c7098ca0368ac8a02f7b437c955975) to democratize access to quantum technologies and accelerate their commercial adoption. They partner with and are trusted by the best quantum, scientific, and infra players.\n\u200d\nInitially published on Business Wire\nOctober 23, 2023 02:23 PM Eastern Daylight Time\n\u200d\n### Begin Your Journey Today to Prepare for the Era of Quantum Technology!\nEmbrace the Quantum revolution with BlueQubit today and step into a world where innovation knows no bounds!\n[JOIN NOW! ![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/639acb0f16d4d943650fe023_Arrow-Right.svg)](https://app.bluequbit.io/?utm_source=landing_blog)\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/63d75ce0dcbbdf01df5c574f_Image_banner.svg)![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/63d75d1f3d52f549fc71000b_Image_banner_mob.svg)\nNo items found.\n###### Company\n[Docs](https://app.bluequbit.io/docs)[Blog](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog)[SDK Docs](https://app.bluequbit.io/sdk-docs/index.html)[Contact us](https://www.bluequbit.io/contact-us)[Research](https://www.bluequbit.io/research)[Quantum mechanical model](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog/quantum-mechanical-model)[BlueQubit platform](https://www.bluequbit.io/platform)[Quantum computing simulators](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog/quantum-computing-simulators)[Free access to quantum computers](https://www.bluequbit.io/free-access)[Quantum computing software platforms](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog/quantum-computing-software-platforms)[Quantum computing algorithms](https://www.bluequbit.io/quantum-computing-algorithms)[Quantum computing companies](https://www.bluequbit.io/blog/quantum-computing-companies)\n###### Explore\n###### Services\n###### Resources\n[![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/6745b8a1e32856e841b07003_product-hunt-logo-orange.svg)](https://www.producthunt.com/products/bluequbit/reviews)\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/639a397b9711984d91a35d74/63a042ea84d8d44f97a1cc3e_Group%2097846.svg)\n\u00a92025 by BlueQubit. All rights reserved.\n[ ](https://discord.gg/TkMuBmWhCw?utm_source=Discord%20Widget&utm_medium=Connect)\n",
